---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Mercury — Red Team Kitchen"
  description="Mercury is Red Team Kitchen's Gemma 4 Good local-agent experiment and Hermes fork archive. The current recommendation is to use Hermes directly rather than maintain our own fork."
>
  <article class="wrap">
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="pills">
        <span class="pill gold">Project · Mercury</span>
        <span class="pill brand">Gemma 4 Good Hackathon</span>
        <span class="pill">Hermes fork archive</span>
      </div>
      <h1>A local-agent experiment, <em>wrapped honestly.</em></h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Mercury explored a personal AI agent running through local Gemma models,
        Discord, a dashboard, and the Cortex bridge. The important conclusion is
        pragmatic: maintaining our own long-lived Hermes fork is not worth the
        operational cost right now. Future work should use
        <a href="https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent">Hermes directly</a>
        and keep Red Team Kitchen additions small, documented, and upstreamable.
      </p>
      <div class="ctas">
        <a class="cta primary" href="https://github.com/AlexiosBluffMara/mercury">Mercury GitHub</a>
        <a class="cta" href="https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent">Hermes upstream</a>
        <a class="cta" href="/gemma">Gemma notes</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>What We Accomplished</h2>
      <div class="panel">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Local Gemma routing:</strong> tested Gemma 4 paths on owned hardware and documented the performance/cost tradeoffs.</li>
          <li><strong>Gateway surfaces:</strong> proved out terminal, Discord, and dashboard workflows around a shared local agent state.</li>
          <li><strong>Cortex bridge:</strong> connected the agent stack to the brain-response pipeline and helped produce the viewer/demo artifacts.</li>
          <li><strong>Negative results:</strong> documented when speculative paths and routing promises did not beat simpler local execution.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>What We Are Not Claiming</h2>
      <p>
        Mercury is not a currently hosted public agent and should not be linked as a
        live service. The repo remains useful as a record of the Gemma 4 Good
        experiment, the scripts, the measurements, and the infrastructure lessons.
        The next healthy version should be a thin integration layer around Hermes,
        not a divergent product fork we have to babysit forever.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Repository</h2>
      <p>
        Source stays available at
        <a href="https://github.com/AlexiosBluffMara/mercury">github.com/AlexiosBluffMara/mercury</a>.
        New work should either happen upstream in Hermes or live in small Red Team
        Kitchen adapters with clear boundaries.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero { padding-top: var(--rtk-sp-7); }
  .pills { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--rtk-sp-2); margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-4); }
  .pill {
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: var(--rtk-radius-pill);
    border: 1px solid var(--rtk-border-strong);
    font-family: var(--rtk-font-mono);
    font-size: var(--rtk-fs-xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--rtk-text-muted);
  }
  .pill.brand { color: var(--rtk-cardinal-bright); border-color: var(--rtk-cardinal); }
  .pill.gold  { color: var(--rtk-isu-gold-bright); border-color: var(--rtk-isu-gold); }

  h1 { font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw + 1rem, 4rem); margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-5); }
  h1 em { color: var(--rtk-cardinal-bright); font-style: italic; }
  .lede { color: var(--rtk-text-muted); max-width: 68ch; font-size: var(--rtk-fs-md); margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-6); }

  .ctas { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--rtk-sp-3); margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-8); }
  .cta {
    padding: var(--rtk-sp-3) var(--rtk-sp-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--rtk-border-strong);
    border-radius: var(--rtk-radius-pill);
    color: var(--rtk-text);
    font-size: var(--rtk-fs-sm);
  }
  .cta:hover { background: var(--rtk-surface-2); }
  .cta.primary { background: var(--rtk-cardinal); border-color: var(--rtk-cardinal); color: #fff; }

  section { margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-8); }
  p, .panel li { color: var(--rtk-text-muted); }
  .panel {
    border: 1px solid var(--rtk-border);
    background: var(--rtk-surface-1);
    border-radius: var(--rtk-radius-sm);
    padding: var(--rtk-sp-5);
  }
  .panel ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; }
  .panel li { margin-bottom: var(--rtk-sp-3); }
  .panel strong { color: var(--rtk-text); }
</style>
